Heat oil in large saucepan on medium heat. Add squash, onion and garlic; cook 5 min. or until crisp-tender, stirring occasionally. Add allspice; cook and stir 1 min. Add chicken broth. Bring to boil; cover. Reduce heat to low; simmer 15 min. or until squash is tender. Add, in batches, to food processor container; cover. Blend until smooth. Return to saucepan; cook until heated through, stirring occasionally. Ladle soup into 8 bowls. Add 1 Tbsp. sour cream to each serving; swirl slightly. Serve with crackers.